mainScore.label: Overall Score
mainScore.description: Candidate can handle many utterances using a variety of words and structures, and can follow and sometimes participate in a native-paced conversation. Pronunciation is mostly intelligible; candidate can express some composite information on familiar topics to a cooperative listener. Candidate understands texts using a variety of words and structures, and given enough time can produce written texts for general purposes. Writing contains errors or inappropriate word choice, but the message is clear to a sympathetic reader.

basicSkills.label: Speaking
basicSkills.description: Candidate produces some simple sentences. Candidate speaks with irregular phrasing or rhythm and mispronounces many consonants and vowels, resulting in a strong, intrusive non-English accent.

basicSkills.label: Listening
basicSkills.description: Candidate understands simple everyday conversational speech when it is spoken clearly and directed at him/her.

basicSkills.label: Writing
basicSkills.description: Candidate writes clear, connected texts on a variety of subjects using a sufficient range of grammatical structures and a good range of common English words.

basicSkills.label: Reading
basicSkills.description: Candidate reads, understands and responds to simple written texts, but has difficulty dealing with more complex texts.
